defaultDistrict Energy systems are systems that produce hot or chilled water at a central source for distribution through a network of below ground
default pre-
default insulated pipework to consumers connected to the energy network system. W
defaulthilst the term community energy has been used in the past to mean district energy, it is now only used to refer to local energy systems of any type that have been implemented by community groups.                                                             
