defaultQuestion:default 
defaultShould the government take any further any specific actions in relation to cooling?default&#xa0;
defaultResponse:default defaultAs the wider effects of climate change begin to translate into more frequent episodes of very high 
defaulttemperatures over the UK summer period, there is a need for greater focus on the provision of efficient cooling systems
default.
default Although the Government has rightly focused on the provision of low cost
default and low carbon
default heating, the UKDEA believes that Government can
default do more with respect to the provision of efficient cooling. The Energy Performance of Buildings Directive makes provision for strategies that enhance the thermal performances of buildings during the summer period (to be given priority) so as to avoid issu
defaultes such as overheating.
default In addition to increased emphasis on passive cooling techniques, district cooling may provide an efficient means of cooling both old and new building stock.
default Economies of scale mean that large scale district cooling plant can achieve
default substantial carbon and cost savings compared to a proliferation of small scale
default air-conditioning split units in urban areas.
