defaultQuestion: What are the relative merits of using gas to directly provide space heating compared to centralised electricity productidefaulton plus domestic heat pumps?   default&#xa0;defaultResponse:default defaultThe use of electricity
default alone
default in the provision of space heating is not a sensible option. Using ce
defaultntralised electricity
default and domestic heat pumps to provide space heating (in place of gas and other energy sources) would result in the
default failure of the electricity grid to 
defaultcope with the
default resulting
default increased demand placed on it especially during times of high heat demand such as th
defaulte cold winter period
defaults
default. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultFig 2default: Showing a comparison
default of national
default heat and electricity demand variability across a year (domestic and commercial)-2010.
defaultSourcedefault:
default 
defaultDECC,
default The Future of Heating: A strategic framework for low carbon heat in the UK
default, March 2012
default. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe use of gas to provide space heating therefore still has signi
defaultficant merit as it substantially
default reduces demand on an electricity grid already struggling to cope with existing demand
default as illustrated in Figure 2 above. In addition the e
defaultfficient use of tech
defaultnologies such as gas fuelled CHP can still achieve substantial carbon emissions savings 
defaultcompared to conventional
default heat sources.
defaultThe use of electricity alone in the provision of space heating could also lead to an increase in the levels of fuel poverty due t
defaulto the high and increasing cost of electricity.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultLow carbon heat generation 
defaultsystems
default such as district heating which
default are largely fuelled by gas can
default therefore play a
defaultn increasingly
default significant role in helping stabilise and reduce
default demand on the
default electricity gri
defaultd. 
defaultAs heat networks can be powered by a wide range of fuels such as biomass
default and deep geothermal (in some cases)
default this makes them an even more attractive option for supplying space heating relative to centralised electricity and heat pumps which place a mas
defaultsive demand on the electricity grid.
default More importantly, due to their fuel agnostic nature heat networks and similar schemes started with gas fired CHP as the principal fuel source can be continually decarbonised 
defaultthrough the  greater use of renewable heating
default technologies as they expand and grow.
